50|$|Erythrite {{crystallizes}} in the monoclinic {{system and}} forms prismatic crystals. The color is crimson to pink and occurs as a secondary coating known as <b>cobalt</b> <b>bloom</b> on cobalt arsenide minerals. Well-formed crystals are rare, {{with most of}} the mineral manifesting in crusts or small reniform aggregates.|$|E
